{"key":"post-8799983","value":"<?xml version=\"1.0\"?>\n<post>\n<id>8799983</id>\n<content>You're supposed to leave the toggle open for the first five to ten minutes that steam is building to allow it to escape.&amp;nbsp; After that, close the toggle and when pressure reaches around 15 psi, use your stove burner control to maintain the correct pressure.&amp;nbsp; Try to keep it in the 13 to 18 psi range.&amp;nbsp; Sterilizers don't automatically regulate pressure the way pressure cookers do.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;There's a safety blowout plug that opens at around 20+ psi depending on model.&amp;nbsp; Only use 3/4&quot; to 1&quot; of water and it will heat up much faster.&lt;br /&gt;RR</content>\n<name>RogerRabbit</name>\n<next>8799988</next>\n<prev>8799817</prev>\n<first>8798246</first>\n<last>10267190</last>\n<when>1219241503</when>\n<utime>08/20/08 05:11 PM</utime>\n</post>"}